 from essbaum rchland vnet ibm com alexander essbaum subject exhaust coating disclaimer this posting represents the poster s views not necessarily those of ibm nntp posting host relva rchland ibm com organization ibm rochester lines two nine since at least one other person was interested in this my fzr s black exhaust pipes are rusty and i researched getting them repaired yesterday i bought a can of vht one five zero zero degree black header paint and spent an hour sanding two of the header pipes by hand sprayed on paint thought about how clean i was able to get the metal with sanding and determined that i wouldn t be at all suprised if the paint wore chipped off in a month soooo call a couple of places up in minneapolis and discover that powder coating while extremely durable will not handle over six zero zero degree temperatures the place i talked to said they were experimenting with some new powder that is supposed to handle one one zero zero degrees but that it wouldn t be available for months at least they directed me to another shop that specializes in header coating the other shop said they have two coatings available one is aluminized that can do one two zero zero degrees and is comparable to powder coating for durability the other is silicon i think based and can do one eight zero zero degrees but is thinner and not as durable both coatings have a textured finish not super smooth and should be cleaned with hot water and a brush price for four one foot header pipes and a two foot four two one collector was one zero zero i m planning to take the parts up friday and get them back ups next week maybe wednesday sounds to me like this kind of coating stuff should be way better than paint considering how much abuse the pipes get from road crap rocks axel